Yep, looks the regression, optimization options:
```js
{
  optimization: {
   // Comment `runtimeChunk` solve the problem
   runtimeChunk: { name: '/manifest'}
   cacheGroups: {
    default: false,
    defaultVendors: false,
    'styles-mycss': {
      name: 'mycss',
      chunks: 'all',
      enforce: true,
      type: 'css/mini-extract',
      test: [Function]
    },
    vendor0: {
      name: '/vendor',
      chunks: 'all',
      enforce: true,
      priority: -10,
      test: /(?<!node_modules)[\\/]node_modules[\\/]()/i
    }
  }
}
```

Entry:
```
entry: {
    '/app': [
      '/path/to/project/src/app.ts',
      '/path/to/project/src/mycss.scss'
    ]
  },
```

i.e. using `mini-css-extract-plugin` + CSS `entry` + `optimization.runtimeChunk` broken
